result.execSummary:
Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Defendant Scott Douglas St Aubin in court, in custody, appearing with Atty. Kevin Schmidt due to Atty. Reid being unable to appear.  William Lund Norine appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Plea agreement recited by Atty. Schmidt, def. will be pleading in 17CF06 to Counts 3 & 5, sentence recommendation would be jail time served and court costs, restitution TBD.  Recess.  Reconvene, $180 restitution agreed to; the amount of $236 is in dispute.  DA & def. agree with Atty. Schmidt's.  Court advised def. of rights being waived and charges being plead to.  Court questions def. as to his version charges, possible discreptancy.  Recess.  Reconvene, Atty. Schmidt reports to the Court that he previously represented a co-defendant and can no longer proceed in representing def.  Court allows Atty. Schmidt to remove himself.  Court questions def. whether he wants to continue with hearing without an attorney or continue hearing until Atty. Reid is present.   Def. waived right to an attorney for today's hearing.  Court finds waiver knowing and voluntarily made. Def. enters a G plea to Counts 3 & 5 in 17CF6.  Court finds plea K&V made, FB found to accept plea.  JOC to be entered finding def. guilty.  Remaining counts and cases will be DRI.  Victim Rights compliance filed with the Court by DA; Recommendation of DA - a time served sentence.  Statement by def. Court orders 118 day (64 days each count), credit for 95 days, time served.  Court orders $443 each ct. court costs.  $1,000 bond to be applied and balance to be applied to $416.43 restitution.  Def. to pay balance at $100 per mo. commencing in 60 days. Appeal rights given & notice of DNA.
No contact at the Holiday South, South Side Auto, Pinewood Motel or Siren Pet Store. $1,000 addiitonal required for release.
